        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 5:06PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 505 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dreher Island State Park, or 12 miles northwest of Highway 6 at Lake
Murray Dam, moving southeast at 20 mph.

...Boaters on Lake Murray Should Seek Safe Harbor...

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbia, Lexington, West Columbia, Irmo, St. Andrews, Highway 6 at
Lake Murray Dam, Red Bank, Oak Grove, Columbia International
University, Harbison State Forest, Dreher Island State Park,
Ballentine, Chapin, Little Mountain, Peak, Oswald Park, Bundrick
Island, Putnam's Landing, White Rock, and Rocky Point Recreation
Area.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 126 near mile marker 0.
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 53 and 65.
Interstate 26 between mile markers 86 and 108.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
